name: Booty Camp
description: This is probably one of the most popular workout names out there, but it's also one of the most eye-roll-inducing. First of all, it's extremely clichéd.

name: Power Hour
description: This workout name sounds more like a math class than a fitness class. It's not very creative or inspiring, and it doesn't give people any indication of what the workout will entail.

name: Fat Burner
description: Again, this is another workout name that sounds more like something you'd find on a weight loss program than in a fitness class.

name: Ab Attack
description: We get it, you want people to work on their abs. But there are much better ways to say it than this! “Core workout” or “ab workout” are both much better options.

name: Sweat & Sculpt
description: This workout name is just too long and convoluted. It's not easy to remember, and it doesn't give people clear workout ideas of what the class will be about.

name: Tone & Trim
description: See above! This is another workout name that's just way too long and complicated. Stick to something simpler and easier to remember.

name: Fat-burning Furnace
description: This workout name is just downright silly. It's not creative, it's not motivating, and it doesn't give people any information about what the workout will entail.

name: Metabolism Booster
description: Again, this workout name sounds more like something you'd find in a weight loss program than in a fitness class. It's not very inspiring, and it could make people feel self-conscious.

name: Body Sculpting
description: This is another popular workout name, but it's also extremely clichéd. And like “booty camp,” it implies that the only reason people would want to work out is to improve the appearance of their entire body.
